==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squeal
<hw>Squeal</hw> <pr>(skw⟦emac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Squealed</conjf>
<pr>(skw⟦emac⟧ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Squealing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Of Scand. origin; cf. Sw.
<ets>sqv⟦aum⟧la</ets>, Norw. <ets>skvella</ets>. Cf. <er>Squeak</er>,
<er>Squall</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To cry with a sharp, shrill,
prolonged sound, as certain animals do, indicating want, displeasure, or
pain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To turn informer; to betray a secret.</def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squeal</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Squeal
<hw>Squeal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A shrill, sharp, somewhat prolonged
cry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squealer</ent>⟦br⟧
